Sentencas: In the present work, high-temperature cyclic oxidation of ferritic stainless steel (FSS) with minor addition of Nb and Ti elements has been carried out at 800 degrees C in air for 70 cycles.
Titulo: High temperature cyclic oxidation behavior of ferritic stainless steel with addition of alloying elements Nb and Ti for use in SOFCs interconnect

Sentencas: Thermal cycling consists of 1 h heating in furnace followed by 15 min cooling to room temperature outside the furnace.
Titulo: High temperature cyclic oxidation behavior of ferritic stainless steel with addition of alloying elements Nb and Ti for use in SOFCs interconnect

Sentencas: The weights of all the specimens were measured every 1 cycle.
Titulo: High temperature cyclic oxidation behavior of ferritic stainless steel with addition of alloying elements Nb and Ti for use in SOFCs interconnect

Sentencas: The specimens were examined by scanning electron microscopy (SEM) and Energy dispersive X-ray spectroscopy (EDS).
Titulo: High temperature cyclic oxidation behavior of ferritic stainless steel with addition of alloying elements Nb and Ti for use in SOFCs interconnect

Sentencas: The purpose of making this alloy was for application in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) interconnects.
Titulo: High temperature cyclic oxidation behavior of ferritic stainless steel with addition of alloying elements Nb and Ti for use in SOFCs interconnect

Sentencas: The addition of minor alloying elements, especially Nb, led to formation of Laves phases in oxide/metal interface and prevented the diffusion of cation to the oxide scale.
Titulo: High temperature cyclic oxidation behavior of ferritic stainless steel with addition of alloying elements Nb and Ti for use in SOFCs interconnect

Sentencas: It is also a barrier for the influence of the oxygen anion to the inward of the FSS.
Titulo: High temperature cyclic oxidation behavior of ferritic stainless steel with addition of alloying elements Nb and Ti for use in SOFCs interconnect

Sentencas: The presence of high amount of Nb and low amount of Ti were effective on improving of the oxidation.
Titulo: High temperature cyclic oxidation behavior of ferritic stainless steel with addition of alloying elements Nb and Ti for use in SOFCs interconnect

Sentencas: By increasing amount of Ti compare to Nb in this steel caused the increased oxidation rate.
Titulo: High temperature cyclic oxidation behavior of ferritic stainless steel with addition of alloying elements Nb and Ti for use in SOFCs interconnect
